work.work-title: Lord, Thou has won, at length I yield

credit.credit-words: If Thou hadst bid Thy thunders roll, And light'nings flash, to blast my soul, I still had stubborn been; But mercy has my heart subdued, A bleeding Savior I have viewed, And now I hate my sin.
Lord, Thou has won, at length I yield
